Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses iterative decoding and linear programming decoding, which are common techniques in information theory. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the convergence of decoding algorithms, which is related to computational complexity. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the structure of parity-check matrices and their effect on error performance, which is related to data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses Tanner graphs, which are commonly used to model social and information networks. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses error performance in codes, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture.
